==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gayly
<hw>Gay"ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <altsp>[Also spelled
<asp>gaily</asp>.]</altsp> <sn>1.</sn> <def>With mirth and frolic;
merrily; blithely; gleefully.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Finely; splendidly; showily; <as>as, ladies
<ex>gayly</ex> dressed; a flower <ex>gayly</ex> blooming.</as></def>
<rj><au>Pope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gayne</ent>⟦br⟧
